    "body": "In a similar vein to #3957, this PR allows the use of local `node_modules` executables for some of the most common tools in the JS ecosystem.\r\n\r\nSome of the tools already had support for this (`biome`,  `glint`, `oxfmt`, `oxlint` and `tsgo`), so for these the code was just slightly refactored to use the new `lspconfig.utils` function `get_node_modules_executable`.",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-12T15:00:06Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pull/4386#discussion_r3068117529"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pulls/4386"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pulls/comments/3068117529"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "thanks for the code re-use effort, but configs in nvim-lspconfig are intended to be fully self-contained, so we do not want to agument `util.lua`. and it looks like this code could be simplified anyway. \n\nnote that `vim.fs.joinpath()` could be used and it accepts `nil` args",
            "commit_id": "ec6dbf2f94d6489ee4240e0686d5d730a0ed9714",
            "created_at": "2026-04-11T14:01:13Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -101,6 +101,14 @@ function M.get_typescript_server_path(root_dir)\n   return ''\n end\n \n+function M.get_node_modules_executable(cmd, root_dir)\n+  local local_cmd = root_dir and root_dir .. '/node_modules/.bin/' .. cmd\n+  if local_cmd and vim.fn.executable(local_cmd) == 1 then\n+    return local_cmd",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/pull/4386#discussion_r3068117529",
